1
00:00:37,633 --> 00:00:40,333
Manuel, you got me pregnant.

2
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:42,000
That's impossible!

3
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:44,067
That child isn't mine!

4
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:49,000
Manuel, is that woman
telling the truth?

5
00:00:49,133 --> 00:00:50,833
Felma, wait. I'll explain.

6
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:53,267
He wanted to marry me
because I'm pregnant!

7
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:55,600
How will you tell the kids
about it?

8
00:00:55,733 --> 00:00:57,167
The kids must not know.

9
00:00:57,300 --> 00:00:59,067
See? That's so close!

10
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:00,867
Jopet has new shoes.

11
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,733
I'll ask my dad to get me
the same shoes.

12
00:01:02,867 --> 00:01:03,800
How can he get home?

13
00:01:03,933 --> 00:01:05,833
He has a new kid in
Saudi Arabia.

14
00:01:05,967 --> 00:01:06,867
Is that so?

15
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,700
Mom, is it true? Did Dad have
another child?

16
00:01:09,867 --> 00:01:11,500
Bro, I need to talk to Felma.

17
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:13,033
She might not answer your call.

18
00:01:13,167 --> 00:01:15,200
How will I tell the kids?

19
00:01:15,333 --> 00:01:16,433
They already know.

20
00:01:16,567 --> 00:01:17,367
How did it happen?

21
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:18,867
- Your dad.
- Dad, is it true?

22
00:01:20,467 --> 00:01:21,533
I'm sorry, dear.

23
00:01:21,967 --> 00:01:24,233
<i> Then, is it true?</i>

24
00:01:24,367 --> 00:01:25,700
Hazel, my kids already know.

25
00:01:25,833 --> 00:01:26,633
They should just accept

26
00:01:26,767 --> 00:01:27,900
that your relationship with them
is over.

27
00:01:28,033 --> 00:01:29,933
Andrea and Jeff are not other
people. They are my kids!

28
00:01:30,067 --> 00:01:31,367
Your illegitimate kids!

29
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:33,067
I told you to stop!

30
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:37,167
Go ahead, sis.

31
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:38,133
Drink it.

32
00:01:38,267 --> 00:01:39,367
Just try it.

33
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:40,333
Come on.

34
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:42,933
So you can let out all
your resentments.

35
00:01:46,167 --> 00:01:47,767
- Help me!
- What happened?

36
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:49,633
Doc, she fell
on the floor.

37
00:01:49,767 --> 00:01:51,767
No! He pushed me!

38
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:52,833
No, no, no! No!

39
00:01:52,967 --> 00:01:54,867
I didn't mean it.

40
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:55,900
Doc.

41
00:01:56,033 --> 00:01:57,667
Hazel, I'm sorry.

42
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,267
Where does it hurt?

43
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:09,367
You're pregnant?

44
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:10,867
Yes.

45
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,333
Yes!

46
00:02:12,467 --> 00:02:14,433
- Hey.
- We're going to have a kid!

47
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:18,100
That's embarrassing.
Don't be so loud.

48
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:21,167
This is the right time for us
to get married.

49
00:02:21,833 --> 00:02:25,000
Felma, we're going
to be a family.

50
00:02:25,133 --> 00:02:28,033
We're still a family even
if we don't get married.

51
00:02:28,167 --> 00:02:32,267
Yes, but I want to marry you.
It's my dream for you.

52
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:34,100
To give you a church wedding.

53
00:02:34,233 --> 00:02:35,933
It'll only cost us money.

54
00:02:36,633 --> 00:02:39,033
It doesn't have to be grand.
We can have a simple wedding.

55
00:02:39,633 --> 00:02:41,433
What's important is that
we get married.

56
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:44,633
Love, listen.

57
00:02:45,267 --> 00:02:46,200
I'm content.

58
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,867
Now that we're having a kid,

59
00:02:49,367 --> 00:02:53,267
my dream of having a family will
be fulfilled.

60
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:55,300
That's enough for me.

61
00:02:56,267 --> 00:02:57,533
I'm happy with it.

62
00:03:08,233 --> 00:03:10,600
Here's your favorite.

63
00:03:11,267 --> 00:03:14,233
Love, I know what name
we will give our kid.

64
00:03:14,767 --> 00:03:15,433
What?

65
00:03:15,933 --> 00:03:16,733
Felmo.

66
00:03:17,467 --> 00:03:18,867
Felmo?

67
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,633
I don't think that sounds good.

68
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:21,933
Felmo?

69
00:03:22,767 --> 00:03:24,867
I want him to
take after you.

70
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,067
Hardworking, kind, and caring.

71
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,767
Come on. Stop flattering me.

72
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:32,333
I'm serious. I'm so lucky
to have you.

73
00:03:33,167 --> 00:03:35,033
That's why I love you so much.

74
00:03:35,167 --> 00:03:36,567
I love you so much, too.

75
00:03:46,333 --> 00:03:48,633
Hi, baby.

76
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:53,033
Love.

77
00:03:53,167 --> 00:03:56,367
Can we now get married?
We're having three kids now.

78
00:03:59,433 --> 00:04:01,100
Yes, we will have three.

79
00:04:01,933 --> 00:04:05,333
They're growing up, and their
needs are increasing.

80
00:04:06,233 --> 00:04:09,867
Love, how many times have we
already talked about marriage?

81
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,667
Let's prioritize the kids.

82
00:04:13,067 --> 00:04:16,533
Yes, I prioritize them. That's
why I want us to get married.

83
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:20,500
I want our family to have
God's blessing.

84
00:04:23,167 --> 00:04:25,933
You saw what happened to
my parents, didn't you?

85
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:31,000
They married. They had God's
blessing. But what happened?

86
00:04:31,933 --> 00:04:33,600
They separated in the end.

87
00:04:35,633 --> 00:04:39,900
Love, God blessed
our relationship.

88
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:41,633
You know why?

89
00:04:42,267 --> 00:04:46,633
Because we're happy. And so are
our kids.

90
00:04:46,767 --> 00:04:49,600
That's what matters most, right?

91
00:04:53,033 --> 00:04:54,700
Dad.

92
00:04:54,833 --> 00:04:57,600
Let's play hide and seek,
but you'll be the "it"?

93
00:04:57,733 --> 00:04:59,333
You want me to join you,
but I'll be the "it"?

94
00:04:59,467 --> 00:05:00,733
Yes.

95
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:01,867
That's unfair.

96
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:02,933
Come on, Dad.

97
00:05:03,067 --> 00:05:05,000
- Let's go. Let's play.
- Okay, okay. Fine.

98
00:05:05,133 --> 00:05:08,367
Hide and seek, the moon is
bright.

99
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,300
By the time I count to ten,
you all should be hidden.

100
00:05:10,433 --> 00:05:12,833
Shouldn't you be
the one counting?

101
00:05:12,967 --> 00:05:14,200
- Go.
- Don't cheat.

102
00:05:14,333 --> 00:05:16,733
- Go on and hide.
- Hide!

103
00:05:16,867 --> 00:05:19,367
Your dad's coming!

104
00:05:27,133 --> 00:05:33,533
Did I make a mistake by
not marrying Manuel?

105
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:39,100
Sis, if you got married,

106
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:43,233
that loose woman couldn't steal
him from you.

107
00:05:43,533 --> 00:05:49,067
But I can't blame you for
not believing in marriage.

108
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,667
Let it go. Forget about it.

109
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,433
Stop regretting it.
It's already done.

110
00:05:56,567 --> 00:05:57,467
Right?

111
00:05:59,733 --> 00:06:02,367
I feel a sense of loss

112
00:06:03,067 --> 00:06:06,067
over the beautiful memories
Manuel and I had.

113
00:06:07,133 --> 00:06:11,333
It feels like a dream.

114
00:06:13,967 --> 00:06:16,067
It's like a dream.

115
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,500
A nightmare.

116
00:06:19,633 --> 00:06:21,467
I want to wake up from it.

117
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:26,567
I want us to go back to
how we were.

118
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:28,333
That time before Manuel
went to Saudi Arabia.

119
00:06:28,467 --> 00:06:30,567
Those times when we were happy.

120
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:33,000
- Do you get it?
- Yes.

121
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:39,767
Sis.

122
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:42,200
We can no longer bring
that back.

123
00:06:42,367 --> 00:06:44,433
We can't, sis.

124
00:06:44,567 --> 00:06:45,433
Move forward.

125
00:06:46,567 --> 00:06:47,633
Forge on.

126
00:06:47,767 --> 00:06:51,900
Sis, are we really over?

127
00:06:52,033 --> 00:06:55,600
I still can't believe it.

128
00:06:55,733 --> 00:07:00,600
So this is all it took for us
to end?

129
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:02,233
No, no, sis. Listen.

130
00:07:02,367 --> 00:07:04,233
It's not over yet between
the two of you.

131
00:07:04,367 --> 00:07:06,400
Just because you're no
longer together

132
00:07:06,533 --> 00:07:09,567
doesn't mean he stops being your
kids' dad.

133
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:11,200
That's it, sis.

134
00:07:11,333 --> 00:07:12,867
Think about it.

135
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,533
You still have kids.

136
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:19,033
So, you must fight for your
kids' right to their father.

137
00:07:19,167 --> 00:07:24,000
My godchildren need financial
support from their dad.

138
00:07:24,133 --> 00:07:26,300
Use it. Always remember that.

139
00:07:26,433 --> 00:07:30,133
You need to fight for
your kids' rights.

140
00:07:30,267 --> 00:07:32,567
It isn't over yet. No.

141
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:35,133
You have kids. Right?

142
00:07:51,233 --> 00:07:52,800
Tell me, Hazel.

143
00:07:52,933 --> 00:07:55,200
Did your husband
really push you?

144
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:00,400
Tell me, Hazel.

145
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:02,533
Did your husband really
push you?

146
00:08:05,367 --> 00:08:09,867
If he has hurt you in any other
way, you can tell me.

147
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:13,500
I can help you report him
to the authorities.

148
00:08:15,367 --> 00:08:16,333
No, Doc.

149
00:08:16,933 --> 00:08:18,433
There's no need to do that.

150
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:22,267
The truth is,

151
00:08:23,300 --> 00:08:24,800
we just had an argument.

152
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:27,567
He didn't really mean
to push me.

153
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:32,867
Doc,

154
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:35,267
how is the baby?

155
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:37,300
The baby is fine, Mr. Cruz.

156
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:39,833
It was a threatened miscarriage.

157
00:08:41,133 --> 00:08:41,867
What?

158
00:08:42,567 --> 00:08:44,633
She said I almost lost the baby.

159
00:08:45,867 --> 00:08:48,700
Your wife had premature
contractions,

160
00:08:49,133 --> 00:08:51,333
but we've given her medication
for it.

161
00:08:51,467 --> 00:08:53,367
And we've also stopped
the bleeding.

162
00:08:53,767 --> 00:08:57,533
Right now, bed rest
is what's best for her.

163
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:01,767
And please, try not to stress
the patient.

164
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:03,833
I did not mean to stress her.

165
00:09:06,367 --> 00:09:07,300
That's her.

166
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:09,567
That's your baby girl.

167
00:09:11,833 --> 00:09:14,367
Doctor Reynolds, urgent call
for you.

168
00:09:16,033 --> 00:09:17,367
Please excuse me.

169
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:18,867
Thank you, Doc.

170
00:09:22,667 --> 00:09:23,867
See what happened?

171
00:09:26,433 --> 00:09:31,200
We would no longer see our baby
girl if I had a miscarriage.

172
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:34,133
Manuel,

173
00:09:35,467 --> 00:09:38,067
I didn't tell them
that you pushed me.

174
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:41,533
But this must not happen again.

175
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,567
Please.

176
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,533
Please, let's not
fight anymore...

177
00:09:50,567 --> 00:09:52,367
for the sake of our baby.

178
00:10:09,467 --> 00:10:13,367
Can I have an official receipt
of the doctor's fee?

179
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:15,600
We can only give you
a temporary receipt.

180
00:10:15,733 --> 00:10:18,033
You need to get it
from her clinic.

181
00:10:18,167 --> 00:10:18,800
Thank you.

182
00:10:18,933 --> 00:10:19,867
You're welcome.

183
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:24,800
- Peace be with you.
- Peace be with you, too.

184
00:10:24,933 --> 00:10:28,067
Payment for patient Hazel Cruz.

185
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,600
Just wait.

186
00:10:32,933 --> 00:10:36,767
Bro, haven't you thought
about the possibility

187
00:10:36,933 --> 00:10:41,400
of getting yourself free if
Hazel had a miscarriage?

188
00:10:43,167 --> 00:10:44,333
Are you crazy?

189
00:10:44,667 --> 00:10:47,067
It's the same as wishing
to lose the baby.

190
00:10:48,933 --> 00:10:51,133
Come on. It's not like that.

191
00:10:52,033 --> 00:10:54,967
I don't want to lose my child.

192
00:10:55,900 --> 00:10:57,900
I saw her very much alive.

193
00:10:59,167 --> 00:11:02,733
I wouldn't forgive myself if
something happened to the baby.

194
00:11:03,633 --> 00:11:05,800
Hazel and I made a mistake.

195
00:11:05,933 --> 00:11:08,300
But that doesn't mean that
the baby should suffer.

196
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:12,033
She's my child, bro. She has
the right to live.

197
00:11:12,167 --> 00:11:14,633
And I want her to live.

198
00:11:27,667 --> 00:11:28,767
You know what, Alice?

199
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:33,333
I saw in Manuel's eyes
that he loves my baby.

200
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:38,200
You wouldn't know that
if you didn't have

201
00:11:38,333 --> 00:11:39,700
a threatened miscarriage.

202
00:11:41,867 --> 00:11:44,033
Maybe it's a blessing
in disguise.

203
00:11:44,867 --> 00:11:47,100
Manuel and I had a fight, and
he unintentionally pushed me.

204
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:49,667
But I don't want that
to happen again.

205
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:52,367
I don't want to fight
Manuel anymore.

206
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:55,767
I don't want to risk our baby.

207
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:01,733
Is the mother in you talking?

208
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:07,067
This baby is softening
Manuel up.

209
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:12,067
If I cooperate and stop
fighting him,

210
00:12:12,533 --> 00:12:14,667
maybe it'll be easier to get
what I want.

211
00:12:16,333 --> 00:12:19,100
And that is for him to forget
Felma and her kids.

212
00:12:21,267 --> 00:12:24,300
My baby and I will be
his only family.

213
00:12:28,267 --> 00:12:29,767
Dear, let's go.

214
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:32,867
You're always messing around.

215
00:12:40,967 --> 00:12:43,367
- That looks delicious.
- I cooked for you.

216
00:12:44,433 --> 00:12:45,667
That's delicious. Try it.

217
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:48,000
Wow. Chicken liver.

218
00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:50,267
- Rich in iron.
- Yes.

219
00:12:50,933 --> 00:12:52,733
That's good for our baby.

220
00:12:52,867 --> 00:12:54,067
And that's what I
often cooked

221
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,200
when she's pregnant...

222
00:13:03,667 --> 00:13:04,500
I'm sorry.

223
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:10,133
Come on. Sit down.

224
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:11,667
Eat with me.

225
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:18,733
Come on. Let's eat together.

226
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:27,133
Let me do it.

227
00:13:36,467 --> 00:13:38,767
Here. I know this
is your favorite.

228
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:42,567
Thank you.

229
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:45,700
There.

230
00:13:46,833 --> 00:13:48,300
Go on and eat.

231
00:13:48,433 --> 00:13:52,133
- Try my cooking.
- Of course, I will.

232
00:14:13,533 --> 00:14:16,367
Manuel? Aren't you going to
sleep yet?

233
00:14:17,867 --> 00:14:18,967
Go and sleep first.

234
00:14:19,467 --> 00:14:21,900
You know that it's not good for
pregnant women to stay up late.

235
00:14:22,033 --> 00:14:22,767
Let's go.

236
00:14:23,633 --> 00:14:25,167
I'll just finish this.
Then I'll follow you.

237
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:26,833
Promise?

238
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:29,667
Don't take too long.

239
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:31,400
Good night.

240
00:14:57,033 --> 00:14:57,867
Hello?

241
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:11,767
So, how's my former love who
already loves someone else now?

242
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:15,667
Felma?

243
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:17,867
Are you drunk?

244
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:23,567
So what?

245
00:15:24,133 --> 00:15:25,800
So what if I'm drunk?

246
00:15:28,967 --> 00:15:31,633
Felma, you don't drink.

247
00:15:36,667 --> 00:15:40,167
People change, right?
They change!

248
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:44,633
Just like you, you changed.
Right?

249
00:15:45,367 --> 00:15:46,600
<i> You love someone else now.</i>

250
00:15:46,733 --> 00:15:50,033
I don't love, Hazel. You're the
one I love. You know that.

251
00:15:50,633 --> 00:15:51,867
<i> I'm drunk,</i>

252
00:15:52,733 --> 00:15:55,900
but I'm not dumb.

253
00:15:57,000 --> 00:16:00,400
You wouldn't marry that woman

254
00:16:01,467 --> 00:16:06,500
if you didn't have any feelings
for her.

255
00:16:06,633 --> 00:16:08,700
Do you want me to explain
it again?

256
00:16:09,533 --> 00:16:11,133
I won't get tired of explaining

257
00:16:11,267 --> 00:16:14,400
until you understand
why I married Hazel.

258
00:16:14,533 --> 00:16:15,633
No!

259
00:16:19,167 --> 00:16:21,867
I don't want to hear your lies!

260
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:25,333
<i> I just called for our kids.</i>

261
00:16:25,733 --> 00:16:27,367
Why? Is there a problem again?

262
00:16:29,367 --> 00:16:32,200
What will happen to them?

263
00:16:32,967 --> 00:16:36,567
<i> What about their needs?</i>

264
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:37,900
<i> Tell me, Manuel.</i>

265
00:16:38,233 --> 00:16:42,867
I will take care of you. I will
continue supporting you.

266
00:16:43,767 --> 00:16:45,167
But what about your wife?

267
00:16:45,767 --> 00:16:47,533
Is it okay with her?

268
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:49,633
<i> Have you talked to her?</i>

269
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:51,800
Have you already talked
about this?

270
00:16:54,633 --> 00:16:55,500
Manuel.

271
00:16:57,533 --> 00:16:58,867
<i> Manuel.</i>

272
00:16:59,467 --> 00:17:02,967
Manuel, I feel like a mistress
begging for your support

273
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:09,867
even though we're your first
family.

274
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:17,033
Come on, Felma.

275
00:17:18,133 --> 00:17:19,500
What's done is done.

276
00:17:20,933 --> 00:17:23,000
There's nothing we can do.

277
00:17:24,633 --> 00:17:27,433
I'll support you. I will keep
sending you money.

278
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:29,600
But that's not what we need.

279
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:35,467
I mean, the children.

280
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:38,000
<i>You need to be a father to them.</i>

281
00:17:38,733 --> 00:17:41,233
I know. Nothing will change.

282
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:44,633
I will still call you.

283
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:47,500
And I will still write
the kids letters.

284
00:17:48,467 --> 00:17:52,433
Felma, they will still feel that
they have a father.

285
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:55,333
I will do my best.

286
00:17:55,467 --> 00:17:57,100
Once I'm done paying off my
debt,

287
00:17:57,233 --> 00:18:00,000
I'll try to come home
to see you.

288
00:18:01,167 --> 00:18:04,600
I don't know how I will tell
your kids.

289
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:07,567
I'm not sure if I have
to tell them.

290
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:10,100
<i>They might only get their hopes
up for nothing.</i>

291
00:18:10,233 --> 00:18:11,300
Felma, please.

292
00:18:13,433 --> 00:18:14,933
Felma, I promise you.

293
00:18:15,067 --> 00:18:16,267
<i> Don't make a promise.</i>

294
00:18:17,267 --> 00:18:18,567
Just do it.

295
00:18:21,567 --> 00:18:22,667
Hello, Felma?

296
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:25,567
Felma!

297
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,800
Mom?

298
00:19:38,933 --> 00:19:40,767
Mom, please wake up.

299
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:47,367
Mom, I'm sorry for waking
you up.

300
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:50,033
What time is it?

301
00:19:50,867 --> 00:19:52,033
It hurts.

302
00:19:55,933 --> 00:19:57,033
Dear.

303
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:00,600
You're going to be late.

304
00:20:00,733 --> 00:20:03,833
I'm sorry. I wasn't able to cook
for you.

305
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:06,933
It's okay, Mom.

306
00:20:07,067 --> 00:20:09,700
Can we just have
money to buy food?

307
00:20:11,667 --> 00:20:12,733
Wait.

308
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:15,467
Mom.

309
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:17,300
Mom, are you okay?

310
00:20:20,133 --> 00:20:21,900
I'm okay, son.

311
00:20:22,033 --> 00:20:24,233
I'm okay. I'm sorry.

312
00:20:25,900 --> 00:20:27,733
Here's your money.

313
00:20:29,667 --> 00:20:30,833
Where is it?

314
00:20:32,433 --> 00:20:34,933
You might be late. There you go.

315
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:36,667
Thank you, Mom.

316
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:39,767
Coleen's still sleeping.

317
00:20:40,567 --> 00:20:44,067
What? Yes. I got her.

318
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:45,300
Be safe, okay?

319
00:20:45,433 --> 00:20:46,733
We'll get going.

320
00:20:48,033 --> 00:20:49,333
Okay. Go on.

321
00:21:37,100 --> 00:21:38,600
Why? What do you want this time?

322
00:21:38,733 --> 00:21:41,133
<i>Won't you really leave
my husband alone?</i>

323
00:21:42,733 --> 00:21:43,633
Hazel?

324
00:21:45,333 --> 00:21:48,367
I told you to stop
calling Manuel.

325
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:53,833
We only talked
about the kids.

326
00:21:53,967 --> 00:21:55,267
<i> About the kids?</i>

327
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:56,433
Or about you?

328
00:21:57,233 --> 00:21:58,700
<i> Stop messing with me, Felma.</i>

329
00:21:59,933 --> 00:22:03,267
Hazel, our children
have needs.

330
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:08,467
<i>That's exactly the reason
Manuel worked abroad.</i>

331
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:11,900
To support the kids. But what
did you do?

332
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:14,233
<i> You seduced him!</i>

333
00:22:14,367 --> 00:22:15,600
You took him away!

334
00:22:15,967 --> 00:22:17,300
I didn't steal him.

335
00:22:17,967 --> 00:22:19,767
It was his own decision
to marry me.

336
00:22:19,900 --> 00:22:22,067
So, I'm now the legal Mrs. Cruz.

337
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:22,867
<i> And you?</i>

338
00:22:23,467 --> 00:22:24,567
<i> You're out of the picture.</i>

339
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:29,833
But if you push yourself
on him, what should I call you?

340
00:22:30,533 --> 00:22:31,833
A mistress?

341
00:22:34,667 --> 00:22:35,933
I'm not a mistress!

342
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:40,633
I was the first Mrs. Cruz.

343
00:22:41,067 --> 00:22:43,800
My children and I are Manuel's
first family!

344
00:22:44,433 --> 00:22:46,567
Well, I'm the one he married.

345
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,833
So, my baby and I are his
legal family.

346
00:22:50,833 --> 00:22:52,700
Our children are still
his children.

347
00:22:53,067 --> 00:22:57,200
<i>They need their father. And
Manuel and I already talked.</i>

348
00:22:57,800 --> 00:23:01,633
He promised me that he would
take care of the kids.

349
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,500
We also talked.

350
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:09,133
And I don't allow him
to support you.

351
00:23:09,467 --> 00:23:11,700
Because I have the right
to my husband's money.

352
00:23:11,833 --> 00:23:14,200
<i>It's not like Manuel
is sending that much.</i>

353
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:18,067
Don't deprive the kids of
what's rightfully theirs.

354
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:18,967
<i> Please!</i>

355
00:23:19,100 --> 00:23:20,700
I'm not dumb!

356
00:23:20,833 --> 00:23:23,733
<i>Don't use the kids to steal
my husband!</i>

357
00:23:23,900 --> 00:23:24,800
You're paranoid!

358
00:23:24,933 --> 00:23:26,833
I'm just putting you
where you belong.

359
00:23:27,300 --> 00:23:29,200
<i>You no longer have any right
to Manuel.</i>

360
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:31,533
My baby and I are his
new family.

361
00:23:31,667 --> 00:23:33,467
<i> We have every right to him.</i>

362
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:36,767
<i>So, stop hoping for any support.</i>

363
00:23:37,100 --> 00:23:38,900
And stop calling, too.

364
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:42,233
<i>I'm sorry, Felma, but you have
no place in his life anymore.</i>

365
00:23:42,867 --> 00:23:45,500
You and Manuel are over.

366
00:24:43,733 --> 00:24:45,567
Why are you drinking?

367
00:24:45,700 --> 00:24:47,067
It helps me, dear.

368
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:52,233
I forget about what your dad
has done, even for a while.

369
00:24:52,367 --> 00:24:54,067
Let me manage your salary.

370
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:56,033
I'll do the budgeting. I'm good
at that.

371
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:58,733
I'm planning to send money
back home.

372
00:24:58,867 --> 00:25:00,700
You can let him have his money.

373
00:25:00,833 --> 00:25:02,200
You have your own salary anyway.

374
00:25:02,367 --> 00:25:03,667
And yours is bigger money.

375
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:05,500
It's not about the money.

376
00:25:05,633 --> 00:25:10,333
He will keep talking with Felma
as long as he supports them.

377
00:25:10,467 --> 00:25:13,433
Before I know it, that woman
might have already stolen him.

378
00:25:13,567 --> 00:25:15,833
I don't know where to start.

379
00:25:15,967 --> 00:25:17,700
I'm here.

380
00:25:17,833 --> 00:25:19,400
I'll help you.

381
00:25:20,500 --> 00:25:23,367
<i> Dad, please come home.</i>

382
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:24,133
Who are you talking to?

383
00:25:24,267 --> 00:25:25,133
Are you talking to your dad?

384
00:25:25,267 --> 00:25:27,067
I told you to stop
talking to him!

385
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:28,233
Mom, please give it to me!

386
00:25:28,367 --> 00:25:29,333
Hello?

387
00:25:29,467 --> 00:25:30,400
<i> - I'm still talking to Dad!
</i>- Hello, Andeng?

388
00:25:30,533 --> 00:25:31,767
Quit it!

389
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:32,800
Andeng! Hello!

390
00:25:32,933 --> 00:25:34,967
We're not allowed to talk to
him, remember?

391
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:36,300
Did you call Felma?

392
00:25:36,467 --> 00:25:38,733
Have you forgotten
what the doctor said?

393
00:25:38,867 --> 00:25:40,467
I can't get stressed.

394
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:43,033
I'll just leave so you
won't get stressed!

395
00:25:43,167 --> 00:25:44,500
You can't leave.

396
00:25:44,633 --> 00:25:45,800
I'm alone here.

397
00:25:45,933 --> 00:25:48,267
What about me? I'm pregnant,
Manuel. You can't!

398
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:49,367
Let go of me!

399
00:25:49,500 --> 00:25:50,633
Manuel!
